cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a novel distributional framework for policy optimization in continuous control, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of off-policy actor-critic methods, which are commonly used in control systems and robotics, further supporting the likelihood of cs.RO and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as potential sub-categories. Finally, the paper includes empirical evaluation using visual inputs, suggesting a possible connection to computer vision and the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision).
